The Java core packages include java.util.zip, which is useful for creating
and reading compressed files or archives in the ZIP and GZIP formats.
This saves you the time of creating custom file archive formats for your
applications.

import java.util.zip.*;


nb java compare string == equals compareto method pointer
Swartz, F. 20001110.  Comparing Strings: ==, .equals(), .compareTo(), â€¦.
Java notes.
http://leepoint.net/notes-java/data/strings/12stringcomparison.html

To compare Strings for equality, don't use ==.  The == operator checks
to see if two objects are exactly the same object.  Two strings may be
different objects, but have the same value (have exactly the same
characters in them).  Use the .equals() method to compare strings for
equality.  Similarly, use the .compareTo() method to test for unequal
comparisons.  For example,

	String s = "something", t = "maybe something else";
	if (s == t)		// Legal, but usually WRONG.
	if (s.equals(t))	// RIGHT
	if (s > t)		// ILLEGAL
	if (s.compareTo(t) > 0)	// CORRECT


